@startuml
title Viaverse Consent / DSAR / Incident — State Diagram

[*] --> CONSENT_UNKNOWN
CONSENT_UNKNOWN --> CONSENT_GRANTED : accept
CONSENT_GRANTED --> CONSENT_WITHDRAWN : withdraw
CONSENT_WITHDRAWN --> CONSENT_GRANTED : re-grant

[*] --> DSAR_OPENED
DSAR_OPENED --> IDENTITY_VERIFIED : verify
IDENTITY_VERIFIED --> PROCESSING : accepted
IDENTITY_VERIFIED --> REJECTED : cannot verify
PROCESSING --> COMPLETED : all receipts received
PROCESSING --> INCIDENT_RAISED : breach/suspicious access
INCIDENT_RAISED --> INCIDENT_RESOLVED : mitigated + reported if needed
INCIDENT_RESOLVED --> PROCESSING : resume DSAR

COMPLETED --> [*]
REJECTED --> [*]

note bottom
Consent withdrawal stops future optional processing;
it may not automatically delete legally required transactional records.
DSAR uses retention/legal-basis policy.
end note
@enduml
